citeinfo.origin: AND International Publishers N.V. (AND Products B.V.)

citeinfo.title: Europe Countries

serinfo.issue: 2006 World, Europe, United States, Canada, and Mexico

citeinfo.othercit: 1) Provides data that originally came from World Vector Shoreline. 2) Provides assistance in coding some attributes.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted the data set (eur_p.shp) from AND Global Road Data. Copied all boundary features inside water bodies from the data set (eur_w_maj.shp). Corrected the projections for a few Arctic islands with data from 2006 Europe Countries. Combined NATION and PROVINCE attributes from AND Global Road Data as the common attribute and joined each of the four provincial lookup tables to the data set. Summarized and dissolved on the country-based attributes merging features to create the country data set. Added the SQKM and COLORMAP attributes and calculated their values. Rearranged, renamed, and removed attributes as needed. Converted the data set to SDC. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.

dataqual.logic: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using either ESRI SDC Data Development Kit Professional 2 (DDKP2) or tools in ArcGIS. The SDC data set is then loaded into ArcSDE® to verify and validate the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
